    {word:"Daunt",pos:"verb",def:"To make someone feel intimidated or apprehensive.",bangla:"ভয় দেখানো বা সাহস ভেঙে দেওয়া।",synonyms:["intimidate","discourage","frighten"],antonyms:["encourage","embolden","inspire"],examples:["The size of the task daunted even the most experienced team members.","Nothing could daunt the determined young athlete."]},
    {word:"Dearth",pos:"noun",def:"A scarcity or lack of something.",bangla:"অভাব বা দুষ্প্রাপ্যতা। কোনো কিছুর পরিমাণ অত্যন্ত কম হলে তাকে dearth বলে।",synonyms:["scarcity","shortage","lack"],antonyms:["abundance","surplus","plenty"],examples:["The drought led to a severe dearth of drinking water in the region.","There is a dearth of qualified teachers in rural schools."]},
    {word:"Debase",pos:"verb",def:"To reduce in quality or value; to degrade.",bangla:"মান বা মূল্য কমানো বা অবনমন করা।",synonyms:["degrade","corrupt","diminish"],antonyms:["elevate","improve","enhance"],examples:["Flooding the market with fake goods debased the brand completely.","The scandal debased his previously sterling reputation."]},
    {word:"Decorum",pos:"noun",def:"Behavior in keeping with good taste and propriety.",bangla:"সামাজিক শিষ্টাচার ও মর্যাদাসম্পন্ন আচরণ।",synonyms:["propriety","etiquette","dignity"],antonyms:["impropriety","indecency","rudeness"],examples:["She maintained her decorum throughout the difficult public hearing.","The students were expected to observe decorum in the assembly hall."]}
