    {word:"Rhetoric",pos:"noun",def:"Language designed to persuade or impress.",bangla:"বাগ্মিতা বা প্রভাবশালী ভাষার কৌশল।",synonyms:["oratory","eloquence","persuasion"],antonyms:["plain speech","silence","bluntness"],examples:["The politician's rhetoric was impressive but his actions were questionable.","She cut through the rhetoric to explain the actual implications of the policy."]},
    {word:"Rudimentary",pos:"adjective",def:"Involving basic facts or principles; undeveloped.",bangla:"মৌলিক ও প্রাথমিক স্তরের।",synonyms:["basic","elementary","primitive"],antonyms:["advanced","sophisticated","complex"],examples:["He had only a rudimentary understanding of how engines work.","The shelter was rudimentary — just four walls and a roof."]},
    {word:"Sagacious",pos:"adjective",def:"Having good judgment; wise.",bangla:"বিচক্ষণ ও প্রজ্ঞাবান।",synonyms:["wise","shrewd","astute"],antonyms:["foolish","naive","shortsighted"],examples:["The sagacious elder advised the young leaders with patience and clarity.","Her sagacious business decisions built the company into an empire."]},
    {word:"Sardonic",pos:"adjective",def:"Grimly mocking or cynical.",bangla:"বিদ্রূপাত্মক ও তিক্ত উপহাস সম্পন্ন।",synonyms:["sarcastic","mocking","cynical"],antonyms:["sincere","gentle","complimentary"],examples:["His sardonic humor made light of the team's disastrous performance.","She offered a sardonic smile when told everything would be fine."]}
  ],
  [
    {word:"Sedulous",pos:"adjective",def:"Showing dedication and diligence.",bangla:"পরিশ্রমী ও নিষ্ঠাবান।",synonyms:["diligent","assiduous","industrious"],antonyms:["lazy","negligent","idle"],examples:["The sedulous student spent every evening preparing for her exams.","His sedulous attention to detail made his work stand out."]},
    {word:"Sycophant",pos:"noun",def:"A person who acts obsequiously to gain advantage.",bangla:"তোষামোদকারী ও চাটুকার।",synonyms:["flatterer","toady","yes-man"],antonyms:["critic","opponent","honest advisor"],examples:["The CEO was surrounded by sycophants who never challenged his decisions.","She despised the sycophants who laughed at every joke the boss made."]},
    {word:"Taciturn",pos:"adjective",def:"Reserved and saying little.",bangla:"মিতভাষী ও কম কথা বলে এমন।",synonyms:["quiet","reserved","reticent"],antonyms:["talkative","garrulous","loquacious"],examples:["The taciturn scientist spoke only when he had something important to say.","Despite being taciturn in public, she was warm and expressive with close friends."]},
    {word:"Tangential",pos:"adjective",def:"Relating to a tangent; not central to the subject.",bangla:"প্রাসঙ্গিক নয় এমন বিষয়ের সাথে সম্পর্কিত।",synonyms:["peripheral","irrelevant","digressive"],antonyms:["central","relevant","direct"],examples:["His tangential remarks confused the meeting agenda.","The documentary veered into tangential storylines that weakened the main narrative."]},
    {word:"Tenacious",pos:"adjective",def:"Holding firmly to something; persistent.",bangla:"অদম্য ও দৃঢ়সংকল্পী।",synonyms:["persistent","determined","resolute"],antonyms:["weak","yielding","irresolute"],examples:["The tenacious researcher refused to give up despite repeated failures.","Her tenacious grip on the ladder saved her from falling."]}
  ],
  [
