    {word:"Vituperate",pos:"verb",def:"To blame or insult someone severely.",bangla:"কঠোর ভাষায় নিন্দা বা গালমন্দ করা।",synonyms:["berate","censure","revile"],antonyms:["praise","commend","flatter"],examples:["The angry customer vituperated the staff in front of other diners.","He was known to vituperate anyone who disagreed with his methods."]},
    {word:"Volatile",pos:"adjective",def:"Likely to change rapidly and unpredictably.",bangla:"অস্থিতিশীল ও অপ্রত্যাশিতভাবে পরিবর্তনশীল।",synonyms:["unstable","unpredictable","erratic"],antonyms:["stable","steady","predictable"],examples:["The volatile political situation made investment risky.","Her volatile temper made every office interaction tense."]}
